Commit Message: Fixed alpha issues. Fixed extra line issue. Changed braille patterns to look nicer.
Added BrailleSegment class and BrailleFlag Enum.
Added get(x,y) helper method to BrailleFlag Enum.
Added calculate_value and calculate_weighted methods to Luminance module.
Fixed gitignore ignoring requirements.txt due to .txt extension
Implemented __slots__ in BrailleSegment to reduce memory consumption.
Added an enum LuminanceMethod to Luminance
Added flag_is_set() and invert() methods to BrailleSegment.
Added type hinting to LuminanceMethod Enum

Due to the way Enum and Classes behave in Python, any function that you give an Enum will act like a method. To remedy this, we have to wrap our functions. Added a wrapper and decorator for this purpose.
BrailleImage now has a from_image class method that will construct a finished BrailleImage from a PIL Image object.
main.py now uses BrailleImage.from_image to construct an image.
Output stream will now be explicitly flushed after write.
Added an extra bitwise AND to BrailleSegment.invert just for security.
Moved argument handling into cli_entry_point(), which then calls main()
Added the program's name to the argument parser.
